          <details>
            <summary>Does my GI Bill pay for all of my tuition?</summary>
            <article>
              <div>
                Your GI Bill pays 100% the cost of tuition. Your GI Bill also
                pays a book stipend of $1000.00 per year while you are enrolled.
              </div>
            </article>
          </details>

          <details>
            <summary>What is my MHA while I am enrolled in school?</summary>
            <article>
              <div>
                Your Monthly Housing Allowance (MHA) is based on the zip code of
                the address for the university. The MHA in 2024 is $2,650.00 per
                month.
              </div>
            </article>
          </details>

          <details>
            <summary>What number do I call to speak to someone?</summary>
            <article>
              <div>
                Call the Military Services Team directly. Arthur J. Bunce at
                631-875-6897 or Jennifere Clayton at 703-786-3775.
              </div>
            </article>
          </details>

          <details>
            <summary>Does UoNA do Fall and Spring semesters?</summary>
            <article>
              <div>
                UoNA operates on seasonal quarters rather than six-month
                semesters. Quarters (Winter, Spring, Summer, and Fall) are ten
                weeks or two and a half months long. There are one to two weeks
                off between quarters.
              </div>
            </article>
          </details>

          <details>
            <summary
              >Can I use Veteran Readiness and Employment (VR&E) funds for
              school?</summary
            >
            <article>
              <div>
                Yes! UoNA works closely with Veteran Readiness and Employment
                (Formerly Vocational Rehab) counselors to facilitate the easy
                enrollment using the funds available. VR and E pays full tuition
                and full MHA for veterans. If you are 10% disabled or higher,
                and have not applied for the funds, call us and we will walk you
                through the application process.
              </div>
            </article>
          </details>

          <details>
            <summary>What is "Hybrid" learning?</summary>
            <article>
              <div>
                In a hybrid learning program, the student does most of the
                coursework remotely with a small in-person component each
                quarter. Beside the in-person component, students work on their
                classes in an asynchronous fashion. That means you do your work
                any time of day or night at your convenience. There are no
                "Zoom" style classes you are required to attend. Professors
                often will schedule extra help classes on weekends but they are
                all voluntary for students.
              </div>
            </article>
          </details>

          <details>
            <summary
              >Am I required to submit other transcripts when I apply to UoNA?</summary
            >
            <article>
              <div>
                Yes. The university and the Veterans Administration (VA) require
                that all students provide transcripts if they attended any other
                college or university. Even if you received "F" grades, we are
                still required to have them on file. It also assists us in
                creating an educational plan for all incoming students. F grades
                will not affect your successful enrollment in the university.
              </div>
            </article>
          </details>

          <details>
            <summary>Do I get college credit for my military training?</summary>
            <article>
              <div>
                Yes. We require all veterans to provide their JST's. We assist
                you in getting them, it's very easy. Some, not all the training
                you did in the military will count as college credits. We work
                very hard to give you as many credits as possible.
              </div>
            </article>
          </details>

          <details>
            <summary
              >Am I required to submit my High School diploma when I apply to
              UoNA?</summary
            >
            <article>
              <div>
                Yes. We ask all incoming students to provide high school
                diplomas. We assist students in this process.
              </div>
            </article>
          </details>

          <details>
            <summary>What kind of degree can I earn at UoNA?</summary>
            <article>
              <div>
                We have a six-month technical diploma, Operations Management for
                Technical Industries (OMTI) program. We have a two-year
                Associate’s Degree in Supervision and Project
                Management (AD-SPM). We have two Bachelor Degree programs, a
                Bachelor of Science in Business Administration (BSBA) and a
                Bachelor of Science in Information Technology (BSIT). We have a
                Post Graduate Certificate Program in Operational Leadership.
                Finally, we have eight Master’s Degree programs. (See full
                descriptions in our UoNA website at www.uona.edu)
              </div>
            </article>
          </details>

          <details>
            <summary>Does my GI Bill pay for textbooks?</summary>
            <article>
              <div>
                Yes. The VA will pay veterans $1000.00 (Per year) for the book
                stipend.
              </div>
            </article>
          </details>

          <details>
            <summary>How fast is the enrollment process?</summary>
            <article>
              <div>
                The enrollment process is fast. It all depends on how fast you
                get your documents and other paperwork completed. We’ve had
                veterans complete it in a day.
              </div>
            </article>
          </details>

          <details>
            <summary
              >What kind of support do I receive from Military Services at UoNA?</summary
            >
            <article>
              <div>
                Our team helps in the enrollment process but we are available to
                help throughout the entire time you are a student at UoNA. We
                pride ourselves in our mentoring program and make it our number
                one job to help veteran students succeed.
              </div>
            </article>
          </details>
        </div>
